    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The thing is, some of the senior linguists are actually pretty worried. They think the new system might lose that \"human touch\"—you know, the idiomatic fluency and cultural nuance you handle so well. They're concerned that while it'll be faster and more precise, it might end up sounding a bit robotic or even missing subtle social cues in high-stakes diplomatic translations. Do you think they have a point?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
